Job Posting Title:   SE_Embedded Software Integration Engineer_Expert
Description:   Expert Software Integration Engineer

At Verification Framework and Integration our mission is to establish an integration and verification environment that enables continuous integration, thus reducing lead time-to-market and increasing product quality. We are responsible for the continuous integration of all internally-developed software and the tool chain at Volvo Trucks Vehicle Software Factory.

We are looking for a Expert Software Integration Engineer for our Hardware Integration Platform Team that are involved in the
Development and maintenance of the verification infra structure. We believe that you have worked with how to manage HIL rigs, IT equipment, Computers and have experience from Platform as a service.
Besides having the technical knowledge, you are expected to be a proactive team player, result oriented, willing to share your knowledge and, at the same time be receptive.

REQUIRED EXPERIENCE
• M.Sc. degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Electrical Engineering or similar
• Fluency in English, both written and spoken
• At least 10 years of experience in embedded software development/CI/IT:
• Linux, Windows, Computers
• Docker
• Ansible
• Dashboards (Kibana, Grafana and similar)
• SAFE Agile, Scrum & Kanban
• PaaS, IaaS
• Firewall knowledge
• Network knowledge
• HIL Rigs
• Maintaining and improving Component and Subsystem rigs
• Jenkins

Personal profile
- Good at communicating/describing items/objects at a high level, but also be able to do it on a low level
- Delivery Focus
- Quality Focus
- Have a great passion for automation
- Interested in hardware and components


== Generic Description of Job ===
Manage and configure the software platform and integrate application software components and the software platform into complete node software. Verify the software platform. This includes software build environment and continuous integration/deployment. The Embedded Software Integration Engineer also develops the embedded software technologies and the software platform. Lead ESW integration in a technical team and play an active role in the delivery. Integrate deliveries from others. Responsibility for securing quality and readiness before release.

The deliveries are often focused on the early phases of the development cycle, developing technical roadmaps. Network across the organization, as well as influencing the work in the other sites. Develop acquired competence, as well as participate in the business development. On Expert level the employee is a recognized expert in Embedded Software Integration Engineering typically obtained through advanced education and work experience.

- Experienced project lead and an established coach, mentor and educator to others in VG
- Known subject matter expert and a natural goto person for complex discipline related issues
- Strong Tshaped profile (either building deeper discipline excellence or developing mature generalist toolbox)
- Known product owner, often contributing to project roadmaps/strategies within context of industry trends
- Clear articulation of value creation by joining up the dots between their work and the TD/BA strategy.

Expert: position typically requires 10 years or more relevant experience

Volvo Group is an equal opportunity employer that values diversity in our workplace and we welcome all applicants regardless of age, ethnicity, gender or cultural background.

Job Posting Start Date:   2024-02-26
Job Posting End Date:   2024-12-31
Location:   Göteborg
Job Family:   Elect. & Electr. Embedded Softw. Eng.
Price: 801 sek/h

